      "content": "Clarithromycin is a strong antibiotic that can dangerously interact with simvastatin by increasing the risk of severe muscle damage. You should absolutely wait at least 3 hours before taking simvastatin after your clarithromycin dose to minimize this risk. Since you're already on simvastatin, you must consult your doctor immediately about switching to a different cholesterol medication while you take the antibiotic.",
